  "name": "Nagaraja COU1 — Orthopedic implant wear credibility assessment (NC-4 negative control)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for finite element (FE) prediction of polyethylene wear in a total knee replacement (TKR) tibial insert under standard gait loading. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can predict relative wear volume for a Class II orthopedic device at Model Risk Level 3. All 13 credibility factors are fully assessed; achieved levels meet or exceed required levels. Sensitivity analysis was performed varying material wear coefficient and contact geometry. Decision: Accepted.",
