        "description": "The quantities of interest (cumulative wear volume, peak contact pressure, wear rate per cycle) must be directly traceable to the clinical decision criterion of wear-related osteolysis risk."
      },
      "rationale": "Cumulative wear volume is the primary QoI linked to UHMWPE particle generation and downstream osteolysis risk. Peak contact pressure is a secondary QoI informing stress-shielding. Both QoIs are explicitly referenced in the predicate device 510(k) submission and ISO 14243-3. Achieved level 2 meets required level 2."
