        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Model form: Archard wear law with cross-shear correction validated against literature",
        "description": "The wear constitutive law (Archard with cross-shear correction factor) must be justified against at least two independent published validation studies for UHMWPE under multidirectional sliding, and model-form uncertainty must be quantified."
      },
      "rationale": "Archard wear law with cross-shear correction (Turell et al. 2003 form) is adopted. Justification references Turell et al. 2003 and Fregly et al. 2005, both demonstrating <10% error for multidirectional UHMWPE wear. Model-form uncertainty estimated via comparison of Archard vs. Saikko wear law predictions (±18% spread); this uncertainty is propagated into the output UQ. Achieved level 3 (quantified model-form uncertainty) exceeds required level 2."
    },
    {
